West Nile fever, Portugal
-----------------------
Information received on 3 Sep 2015 from Prof. Dr Alvaro Mendonca, Director General, Direccao Geral de Alimentacao e Veterinaria, Ministerio da Agricultura E do Mar, Lisboa, Portugal

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 21 Aug 2015
Date of confirmation of the event: 31 Aug 2015
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 13 Jan 2011
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: West Nile virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (3)
Outbreak 1 (WNF001/2015): Loule-CH01, N.a., DSVR Do Algarve
Date of start of the outbreak: 21 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 18 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Horses kept in an equestrian center. Only one horse showed clinical signs, namely ataxia.

Outbreak 2 (WNF003/2015): Loule-CH02, N.a., DSVR Do Algarve
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 10 / 2 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Horses kept in an equestrian center. It was referred by the owner that initially two animals showed clinical signs. One of the animals completely recovered. The other animal still presented mild signs.

Outbreak 3 (WNF002/2015): Loule-CH01, N.a., DSVR Do Algarve
Date of start of the outbreak: 24 Aug 2015
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 54/ 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Horses kept in an equestrian center. Only one horse showed clinical signs and is responding to treatment.

Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 3
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 82 / 4 / 0 / 2 / 0
Outbreak statistics: [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / morbidity rate / mortality rate / case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 4.88 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: vectors, epidemiological investigation ongoing.

Epidemiological comments: A clinical suspicion of a probable case of West Nile fever in a human patient was communicated by the National Health Authority. Clinical, epidemiological and serological surveillance was implemented in order to access the possible presence of West Nile virus in susceptible species in the area. Voluntary vaccination will be implemented in the area. Outbreak at Loule - CH02 is a secondary outbreak related to outbreak at Loule - CH01.

Control measures
Measures applied: disinfection/disinfestations; dipping/spraying; quarantine; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; zoning; control of vectors; no vaccination; treatment of affected animals (symptomatic treatment)
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type:
National Institute for Agrarian and Veterinary Research (INIAV) (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Equidae / antibody detection ELISA/ 31 Aug 2015/ Positive
Equidae/ IGM-capture ELISA/ 31 Aug 2015/ Positive
Equidae/ real-time reverse transcriptase/polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR)/ 31 Aug / Positive
Equidae/ seroneutralization test (SNT)/ 31 Aug 2015

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[For background information on West Nile Fever (WNF) see ProMED-mail report 20150902.3619529.

Portugal reported its 1st human case of WNF in the Algarve municipality, <ttp://tinyurl.com/c7x8elf>. This case occurred in the same municipality where animals cases have been reported. According with the epidemiological comments: "A clinical suspicion of a probable case of West Nile fever in a human patient was communicated by the National Health Authority. Clinical, epidemiological and serological surveillance was implemented in order to access the possible presence of West Nile virus in susceptible species in the area."

The European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control (ECDC), updated 3 Sep 2015, noted that 41 human cases of West Nile fever have been reported in the European Union. 36 cases have been reported in neighboring countries since the beginning of the 2015 transmission season.

Additional information and a map with distribution of West Nile fever human cases by affected area are available at http://tinyurl.com/c7x8elf. - Mod.CRD

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3624767,42.]
